response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Find the First Duplicate\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, write a function that finds the first duplicate in the list. If there are no duplicates, return -1.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_first_duplicate(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of unique integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the first duplicate integer if found, otherwise returns -1.\\n\", \"code\": \"\\ndef find_first_duplicate(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n    seen = set()\\n    for num in nums:\\n        if num in seen:\\n            return num\\n        seen.add(num)\\n    return -1\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_first_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == -1\", \"assert find_first_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 2]) == 2\", \"assert find_first_duplicate([1, 2, 3, 4, 4, 4]) == 4\", \"assert find_first_duplicate([]) == -1\"] }"
